{
  "_comment": "Realism regression baseline for _audit_gate.js. Reproducible because the audits are SEEDED. The gate fails if a metric drifts from 'value' by more than 'tol'. 'nfl' is the audit's own acceptable band (informational warning only, not a failure). Metrics tagged 'fast' run in the pre-commit hook (node _audit_gate.js --fast, mff only, ~1min); the full set (adds the slower _sim_audit benchmarks) runs in CI. Gate is REGRESSION-focused (did an engine/talent change move realism?), not a realism-validity claim — run larger N manually for that (see AUDIT.md). Re-baseline an intentional change by updating 'value' in the same commit. NOTE: rare-event tails (INT rate, turnovers) are deliberately NOT gated — small-sample noisy even seeded.",
  "seed": 1337,
  "metrics": [
    {
      "audit": "_mff_audit.js", "args": ["1"], "fast": true,
      "label": "mff_league_pressure_rate",
      "pattern": "League pressure rate:\\s+([0-9.]+)%",
      "value": 40.0, "tol": 2.5, "nfl": [30, 40]
    },
    {
      "audit": "_mff_audit.js", "args": ["1"], "fast": true,
      "label": "mff_run_block_win_rate",
